description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role: Clinical Nurse Specialist/Paramedic(Nights)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 30 hours per week – (10 hour shifts)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £28716 - £43957 per annum pro rata according to skills and experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Compton, Wolverhampton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compton Care are looking to recruit a Clinical Nurse Specialist to join the Community Services Rapid Response team which provides a clinical, hands on care, service which aims to complement and enhance the care available in the community to those with a rapidly deteriorating life advancing, chronic, incurable illness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be there to offer specialist knowledge, expertise and support to the patient and carer, enabling the patient to stay in their home if that is their wish by helping to prevent hospital admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL CRITERIA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RGN or registered paramedic with 4 years post registration experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Palliative care/relevant degree or working towards that level of education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in palliative and/or community care. The ability to work alone and within a team. Willingness to work long shifts across nights&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A real passion/commitment to providing high quality palliative/end of life care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for applications: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should a high number of applications be received, Compton Care reserve the right to close this role sooner than advertised. Therefore we would encourage all candidates to submit an application as soon as possible to avoid any disappointment.&lt;/p&gt;
